{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1d2b52f3-1748-41d1-9e36-1e2b31f244d4","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theory:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results (not failed), and the reason string appears in the test output so your team knows why.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cc20316a-d190-469c-b78d-ca9a34b46332","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing tools.","outputTokens":206,"requestId":"E3C4:207F19:55EDEA:633622:6A0523D6"},"id":"9624e52a-5295-42e4-9f25-64fcb812efd0","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:22:36.896Z","parentId":"4b5e5dc9-b04b-4501-9bae-57b66b5a636b"}
